***** Session Overview *****
                                        What can happen if the connection
                                        between the brain and the visual system
                                        is disrupted or damaged? What can cause
                                        patients to act as if part of their
                                        world not only doesn't exist, but
                                        couldn't exist? In this lecture, we
                                        will discuss blindsight and neglect and
                                        see how studies on these patients have
                                        provided insights on how our brains
[Satellite image of Earth with the left receive and interpret information about
half nearly blacked out.]               the world.
                                        Keywords: blindsight, neglect,
                                        attention, extinction, visuospatial
                                        agnosia, hemispatial neglect,
                                        anosagnosia, right and left
                                        inattentive, parietal cortex, temporal
                                        cortex, representational theory, M.
                                        Posner.
